Diagnosis.

R. houheensis

can be distinguished from all its congeners by a combination of the following features: predorsal scale series 0 (
Fig. 2
); vertebrae counts 12+18=30 (
Fig. 3
); first dorsal fin rays VI, second dorsal fin rays I/9-I/10 (
Fig. 3
and 
Table 1
); pectoral-fin rays 16–17 (
Table 1
). While alive (
Fig. 4
), the first dorsal fin consists of dark brown spinous rays and transparent fin membrane, the fin membrane with two navy blue stripes and a black spot between the first to the third spinous rays. The pectoral fin was grayish, its basal portion was light-brown.

