subSubSection.paragraph:
Scales
. Body covered with ctenoid scales while mid-trunk scales were enlarged. Anterior predorsal area naked (
Fig. 2
and 
Table 1
). Opercle, preopercle, and pelvic base region scale-less. Longitudinal scale series counted 37–40 (modally 38, 
Table 1
). Transverse scale series rounded 12–14 (
Table 1
).
